                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I probably shouldn't be putting too much stock in what I actually 'see' my pet doing vs. what the combat window spam says, but I figured I'd toss this out there anyway.<br /><br />When camping DL thieves last night, I had given my level 44 pet (Cackling Bones) a pair of summoned daggers.  As he chased down the feared thieves, I could see both his arms stabbing furiously.<br /><br />Today, I have no weapons to give him and now I only see him hitting with his primary.  I turned on his spam to see if I could determine whether or not he's attacking with his secondary, but it just rolls too fast.<br /><br />The pet guide here says my pet should attack with both hands without weapons at this level, but I'm not 'seeing' it.  Is this just a graphics glitch or is something amiss here?<br /><br />Thanks.</span id="msg"></font>
