                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Here. Listen. All pets summoned with Convoke Shadow, or better, will dual-wield automatically, whether or not they are given weapons. The Level 29 pet, Summon Dead, will *appear* to dual-wield when given weapons, as it does equip two weapons. However, this pet does not use the dual-wield skill at all, or so infrequently as to make it a trivial addition to its DPS.<br /><br /><br />Furthermore, to even suggest that giving a pet that dual-wields automatically weapons increases the frequency with which this ability activates is absurd. Go have a chat with a monk. Ask him whether or not he dual-wields more frequently when he uses his bo staves, rather than his fists.<br /><br /><br />I wish this unwitting disinformation policy would be brought to a halt.<br /><br /><br />And, in case you didn't catch what I was saying in the midst of my rant, bud, the Cackling Bones pet will do as much damage with his little fists, as he will with a pair of rusty daggers. His dual-wield ability functions like Monk dual-wield, as well as everyone else's. It works barehanded.<br /><br /><br />The -only- pet that I am aware requires weapons to activate dual-wield is the Shaman pet. Poor, poor shamans. <br /><br /><br />Ciao, pal. Good luck.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> - Baron Demetrii Hopeslayer<br />- Level 62 Warlock<br />- Follower of Cazic-Thule<br />' Life is not the best of things, nor is Death the worst. '</span></font></td>
