                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Incorrect. The Weighted Axe will be equipped and used, and the pet's maximum damage per hit will increase to roughly 110. However, the pet will cease to dual-wield, as the weapon is two-handed. The pet's DPS would suffer as a result, unless the pet is rather low in level -- I.E., the Level 34 or 39 summons. Anything that comes close to the 49 summons would be better off with its fists, or some cheap weapon with a damage proc.<br /><br /><br />Personally, I'm more than happy with the skeleton's bare fists -- I mean, he has a 50 to 75 point Drain DD built in. Why burn platinum on weapons that'll be gone as soon as you zone, or the pet dies? Pointless.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
